quran[25]{c,v,t,f}:
37,52,"who used to say: �Are you also one of those who confirm the Truth (of life after death)?"
37,53,"After we are dead and have become all dust and bones shall we still be requited?' {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,54,"He will say: �Do you wish to know where he is now?'"
37,55,"Then he will look downwards, and will see him in the depths of Hell."
37,56,"He will say to him: �By Allah, you almost ruined me."
37,57,"But for Allah's favour, I should be one of those who have been mustered here. {1}",footnotes:1:This shows how powerful will be man’s hearing
37,58,"So, are we not going to die,"
37,59,"except for our first death? And shall we suffer no chastisement?'” {1}",footnotes:1:The style clearly shows that while speaking to his friend in Hell
37,60,"Surely this is the supreme triumph."
37,61,"For the like of it should the workers work."
37,62,"Is this a better hospitality or the tree of al-Zaqqum? {1}",footnotes:1:Zaqqum is a tree of the cactus species found in Tihamah. It is bitter in taste
37,63,"We have made this tree a trial for the wrong-doers. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,64,"It is a tree that grows in the nethermost part of Hell."
37,65,"Its spathes are like the heads of satans. {1}",footnotes:1:Nobody should have the misunderstanding that since no one has seen the head of Satan
37,66,"(The people of Hell) will surely eat of it, filling their bellies with it."
37,67,"Then on top of it they will have a brew of boiling water."
37,68,"Then their return will be to the same blazing Hell. {1}",footnotes:1:This shows that when the dwellers of Hell will be in distress due to hunger and thirst
37,69,"These are the ones who found their fathers steeped in error,"
37,70,"and they are running in their footsteps."
37,71,"Before them a multitude of people of olden times had erred,"
37,72,"and We had sent among them Messengers to warn them."
37,73,"Observe, then, what was the end of those that had been warned,"
37,74,"except for the chosen servants of Allah? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,75,"Noah {1} had called upon Us (earlier). {2} See, how excellent We were in answering him!",footnotes:1:This theme is related with the preceding sentences. A study of them shows why these stories are being narrated here.This refers to the prayer that the Prophet Noah (peace be upon him) had at last made to Allah Almighty
37,76,"We delivered him and his household from the great calamity; {1}",footnotes:1:That is
